By Hauwa Gold Abuja – Mpape Grade 1 Area Court, Abuja, on Tuesday ordered the remand of Ali Usman and Abubakar Usman, both security men, for allegedly stealing provisions valued at N290,534, belonging to a businesswoman. The judge, Salihu Ibrahim, ordered that Ali Usman,20, be remanded in prison, while Abubakar Usman, 18, should be in police custody. The judge adjourned the case until June 17, for further mention.Earlier, the prosecutor, Mr Austin Urom, told the court that the case was reported at the Mpape Police Station by the complainant, Aishat Shuaibu of opposite Zenith Bank area, Mpape. Urom said the defendants broke into the complainant’s shop and stole provisions value at N290, 534. During police investigation, the defendants denied committing the offence. Urom said that the offence contravened the provisions of Section 287 of the Penal Code. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge